  "title": "QUANTITY SURVEYOR (QS)",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Prepare tender and contract documents, including bills of quantities</li>\n  <li>Able to do cost estimation independently and accurately</li>\n  <li>Taking off quantity for tender</li>\n  <li>Final account preparation</li>\n  <li>Monthly progress claim</li>\n  <li>Certification of sub-contract works</li>\n  <li>Liaise with clients, architects, engineers, surveyors and sub-contractors</li>\n  <li>All other related works</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree / Diploma in Quantity Surveying / Building or equivalent from a recognized University</li>\n  <li>Min 2 - 4 years’ relevant experience</li>\n  <li>Good working knowledge in Residential projects, Building &amp; M &amp; E</li>\n  <li>Good knowledge of local rules and regulations</li>\n  <li>Able to handle take-off, tender etc</li>\n  <li>Only Singaporeans and PR</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Competitive remuneration package commensurate with qualifications will be offered.</strong></p>\n<p>Interested candidates are invited to apply via email with an updated resume, which should include current and expected salaries, date of availability, and a recent photograph in MS Word Format. We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified</p>",
